Neural Networks, Reinforcement Learning

The paper belongs to the sub-categories of Neural Networks and Reinforcement Learning. 

Neural Networks: The paper discusses the use of a specific type of neural network, called AA1, and analyzes its convergence and generalization properties. The authors also compare the performance of AA1 with other neural network models.

Reinforcement Learning: The paper uses reinforcement learning to train the AA1 neural network. The authors describe the use of a reward function to guide the learning process and evaluate the performance of the model on a variety of tasks.
